Abstract:
. Cotangent sums play a signiﬁcant role in the Nyman-Beurling cri-
terion for the Riemann Hypothesis. Here we investigate the maximum of the
values of these cotangent sums over various sets of rational numbers in short
intervals.
Key words: Cotangent sums; Estermann’s zeta function; Riemann zeta func-
tion; Riemann Hypothesis; Kloosterman sums.
